ciscoLwappRFMIB.name: ciscoLwappRFMIB

revisions.description: Add 11n MCS rates support in profile, cLRFProfileMcsDataRateTable is added for this rate setting.

Below new objects have been added to the cLRFProfileTable cLRFProfileHighDensityMaxRadioClients cLRFProfileBandSelectProbeResponse cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleCount cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleThreshold cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireSuppression cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireDualBand cLRFProfileBandSelectClientRSSI cLRFProfileLoadBalancingWindowSize cLRFProfileLoadBalancingDenialCount cLRFProfileCHDDataRSSIThreshold cLRFProfileCHDVoiceRSSIThreshold cLRFProfileCHDClientExceptionLevel cLRFProfileCHDCoverageExceptionLevel cLRFProfileMulticastDataRate One new scalar object has been added cLRFProfileOutOfBoxAPConfig
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoLwappRFMIB.description: This MIB is intended to be implemented on all those devices operating as Central Controllers (CC) that terminate the Light Weight Access Point Protocol tunnel from Cisco Light-weight LWAPP Access Points. This MIB helps to manage the Radio Frequency (RF) parameters on the controller. The relationship between CC and the LWAPP APs can be depicted as follows: +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + CC + + CC + + CC + + CC + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ .. . . . .. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + + + AP + + AP + + AP + + AP + + AP + + + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ + + + + + + + + + + + MN + + MN + + MN + + MN + + MN + + + + + + + + + + + +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ +......+ The LWAPP tunnel exists between the controller and the APs. The MNs communicate with the APs through the protocol defined by the 802.11 standard. LWAPP APs, upon bootup, discover and join one of the controllers and the controller pushes the configuration, that includes the WLAN parameters, to the LWAPP APs. The APs then encapsulate all the 802.11 frames from wireless clients inside LWAPP frames and forward the LWAPP frames to the controller. GLOSSARY Access Point ( AP ) An entity that contains an 802.11 medium access control ( MAC ) and physical layer ( PHY ) interface and provides access to the distribution services via the wireless medium for associated clients. LWAPP APs encapsulate all the 802.11 frames in LWAPP frames and sends it to the controller to which it is logically connected to. Central Controller ( CC ) The central entity that terminates the LWAPP protocol tunnel from the LWAPP APs. Throughout this MIB, this entity also referred to as 'controller'. Light Weight Access Point Protocol ( LWAPP ) This is a generic protocol that defines the communication between the Access Points and the controllers. Mobile Node ( MN ) A roaming 802.11 wireless device in a wireless network associated with an access point. 802.1x The IEEE ratified standard for enforcing port based access control. This was originally intended for use on wired LANs and later extended for use in 802.11 WLAN environments. This defines an architecture with three main parts - a supplicant (Ex. an 802.11 wireless client), an authenticator (the AP) and an authentication server(a Radius server). The authenticator passes messages back and forth between the supplicant and the authentication server to enable the supplicant get authenticated to the network. Radio Frequency ( RF ) Radio frequency (RF) is a rate of oscillation in the range of about 3 kHz to 300 GHz, which corresponds to the frequency of radio waves, and the alternating currents which carry radio signals. Received Signal Strength Indicator ( RSSI ) A measure of the strength of the signal as observed by the entity that received it, expressed in 'dbm'. Coverage Hole Detection ( CHD ) If clients on an Access Point are detected at low RSSI levels, it is considered a coverage hole by the Access Points. This indicates the existence of an area where clients are continually getting poor signal coverage, without having a viable location to roam to. REFERENCE [1] Wireless LAN Medium Access Control ( MAC ) and Physical Layer ( PHY ) Specifications. [2] Draft-obara-capwap-lwapp-00.txt, IETF Light Weight Access Point Protocol [3] IEEE 802.11 - The original 1 Mbit/s and 2 Mbit/s, 2.4 GHz RF and IR standard.

CiscoLwappRFApDataRates.name: CiscoLwappRFApDataRates
CiscoLwappRFApDataRates.description: This field indicates the data rates supported by an AP 'disabled' The rate is not supported by the AP 'supported' The rate is supported by the AP 'mandatoryRate' The rate is required by the AP 'notApplicable' The rate is notApplicable.

cLAPGroupsRFProfileTable.name: cLAPGroupsRFProfileTable
cLAPGroupsRFProfileTable.description: This table lists the mapping between an RF profile and an AP group.

cLAPGroupsRFProfileEntry.name: cLAPGroupsRFProfileEntry
cLAPGroupsRFProfileEntry.description: An entry containing the configuration attributes that affect the operation of the APs within a group. Entries can be added/deleted by explicit management action from NMS/EMS through the 'bsnAPGroupsVlanRowStatus' object in bsnAPGroupsVlanTable as defined by the AIRESPACE-WIRELESS-MIB.

cLAPGroups802dot11bgRFProfileName.name: cLAPGroups802dot11bgRFProfileName
cLAPGroups802dot11bgRFProfileName.description: This object specifies the RF profile name assigned to this site on the 802.11bg radio. This profile being assigned should exist in the 'cLRFProfileTable'. To disassociate a profile with this site a string of zero length should be set.

cLAPGroups802dot11aRFProfileName.name: cLAPGroups802dot11aRFProfileName
cLAPGroups802dot11aRFProfileName.description: This object specifies the RF profile name assigned to this site on the 802.11a radio. This profile being assigned should exist in the 'cLRFProfileTable'. To disassociate a profile with this site a string of zero length should be set.

cLRFProfileTable.name: cLRFProfileTable
cLRFProfileTable.description: This table lists the configuration for each RF profile.

cLRFProfileEntry.name: cLRFProfileEntry
cLRFProfileEntry.description: An entry containing the configuration attributes that affect the operation of 802.11 RF domain. Entries can be added/deleted by explicit management action from NMS/EMS or through user console.

cLRFProfileName.name: cLRFProfileName
cLRFProfileName.description: This object uniquely identifies a RF Profile.

cLRFProfileDescr.name: cLRFProfileDescr
cLRFProfileDescr.description: This object specifies a human-readable description of the profile.

cLRFProfileTransmitPowerMin.name: cLRFProfileTransmitPowerMin
cLRFProfileTransmitPowerMin.description: This object specifies the lower bound of transmit power value supported by an AP.

cLRFProfileTransmitPowerMax.name: cLRFProfileTransmitPowerMax
cLRFProfileTransmitPowerMax.description: This object specifies the uppoer bound of transmit power value supported by an AP.

cLRFProfileTransmitPowerThresholdV1.name: cLRFProfileTransmitPowerThresholdV1
cLRFProfileTransmitPowerThresholdV1.description: This object specifies the transmit power control version 1 threshold for the radio resource management algorithm.

cLRFProfileTransmitPowerThresholdV2.name: cLRFProfileTransmitPowerThresholdV2
cLRFProfileTransmitPowerThresholdV2.description: This object specifies the transmit power control version 2 threshold for the radio resource management algorithm.

cLRFProfileDataRate1Mbps.name: cLRFProfileDataRate1Mbps
cLRFProfileDataRate1Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate2Mbps.name: cLRFProfileDataRate2Mbps
cLRFProfileDataRate2Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate5AndHalfMbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate11Mbps.name: cLRFProfileDataRate11Mbps
cLRFProfileDataRate11Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate6Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate9Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate12Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate18Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileDataRate24Mbps.description: This object specifies the configuration for this data rate.

cLRFProfileRadioType.name: cLRFProfileRadioType
cLRFProfileRadioType.description: This object is used to configure the radio type for this profile.

cLRFProfileStorageType.name: cLRFProfileStorageType
cLRFProfileStorageType.description: This object represents the storage type for this conceptual row.

cLRFProfileRowStatus.name: cLRFProfileRowStatus
cLRFProfileRowStatus.description: This is the status column for this row and used to create and delete specific instances of rows in this table.

cLRFProfileHighDensityMaxRadioClients.name: cLRFProfileHighDensityMaxRadioClients
cLRFProfileHighDensityMaxRadioClients.description: This object specifies the maximum number of clients per AP radio.

cLRFProfileBandSelectProbeResponse.name: cLRFProfileBandSelectProbeResponse
cLRFProfileBandSelectProbeResponse.description: This object specifies the AP's probe response with clients to verify whether client can associate on both 2.4 GHz and 5Ghz spectrum. When set to true, AP suppresses probe response to new clients for all SSIDs that are not being Band Select disabled.

cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleCount.name: cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleCount
cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleCount.description: This object specifies the maximum number of cycles not responding.

cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleThreshold.name: cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleThreshold
cLRFProfileBandSelectCycleThreshold.description: This object specifies the cycle threshold for band select.

cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireSuppression.name: cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireSuppression
cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireSuppression.description: This object specifies the expire of suppression.

cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireDualBand.name: cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireDualBand
cLRFProfileBandSelectExpireDualBand.description: This object specifies the expire of dual band.

cLRFProfileBandSelectClientRSSI.name: cLRFProfileBandSelectClientRSSI
cLRFProfileBandSelectClientRSSI.description: This object specifies the minimum dBM of a client RSSI to respond to probe.

cLRFProfileLoadBalancingWindowSize.name: cLRFProfileLoadBalancingWindowSize
cLRFProfileLoadBalancingWindowSize.description: This object specifies the number of clients associated between APs.

cLRFProfileLoadBalancingDenialCount.name: cLRFProfileLoadBalancingDenialCount
cLRFProfileLoadBalancingDenialCount.description: This object specifies number of clients denial with respect to AP.

cLRFProfileCHDDataRSSIThreshold.name: cLRFProfileCHDDataRSSIThreshold
cLRFProfileCHDDataRSSIThreshold.description: This object specifies the RSSI threshold value for data packets.

cLRFProfileCHDVoiceRSSIThreshold.name: cLRFProfileCHDVoiceRSSIThreshold
cLRFProfileCHDVoiceRSSIThreshold.description: This object specifies RSSI threshold value for voice packets.

cLRFProfileCHDClientExceptionLevel.name: cLRFProfileCHDClientExceptionLevel
cLRFProfileCHDClientExceptionLevel.description: This object specifies the client minimum exception level.

cLRFProfileCHDCoverageExceptionLevel.name: cLRFProfileCHDCoverageExceptionLevel
cLRFProfileCHDCoverageExceptionLevel.description: This object specifies the coverage exception level.

cLRFProfileMulticastDataRate.name: cLRFProfileMulticastDataRate
cLRFProfileMulticastDataRate.description: This object specifies the minimum multicast data rate. A value 0 indicates that AP will automatically adjust data rates.

cLRFProfile11nOnly.name: cLRFProfile11nOnly
cLRFProfile11nOnly.description: This object specifies if 11n-client-only mode is enabled.

cLRFProfileHDClientTrapThreshold.name: cLRFProfileHDClientTrapThreshold
cLRFProfileHDClientTrapThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold number of clients per AP radio to trigger a trap. The trap ciscoLwappApClientThresholdNotify will be triggered once the count of clients on the AP radio reaches this limit. A value of zero indicates that the trap is disabled.

cLRFProfileInterferenceThreshold.name: cLRFProfileInterferenceThreshold
cLRFProfileInterferenceThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold number of interference between 0 and 100 percent.

cLRFProfileNoiseThreshold.name: cLRFProfileNoiseThreshold
cLRFProfileNoiseThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold number of noise threshold between -127 and 0 dBm.

cLRFProfileUtilizationThreshold.name: cLRFProfileUtilizationThreshold
cLRFProfileUtilizationThreshold.description: This object specifies the threshold number of utlization threshold between 0 and 100 percent.

cLRFProfileDCAForeignContribution.name: cLRFProfileDCAForeignContribution
cLRFProfileDCAForeignContribution.description: This object specifies whether foreign interference is taken into account for the DCA metrics.

cLRFProfileDCAChannelWidth.name: cLRFProfileDCAChannelWidth
cLRFProfileDCAChannelWidth.description: This object specifies how the system performs DCA channel width selection for the RFProfile min - Min channel width(20Mhz) the radio supports medium - Medium channel width(40Mhz) supported by this radio. max - Max channel width(80Mhz) supported by this radio.

cLRFProfileDCAChannelList.name: cLRFProfileDCAChannelList
cLRFProfileDCAChannelList.description: This object specifies the 802.11 channels available to the RF Profile. A comma separated list of integers.

cLRFProfileRxSopThreshold.name: cLRFProfileRxSopThreshold
cLRFProfileRxSopThreshold.description: Configures the receiver start of packet threshold for the rf profile.

cLRFProfileOutOfBoxAPConfig.name: cLRFProfileOutOfBoxAPConfig
cLRFProfileOutOfBoxAPConfig.description: This object specifies the out of box AP group.

cLRFProfileMcsDataRateTable.name: cLRFProfileMcsDataRateTable
cLRFProfileMcsDataRateTable.description: This object specifies the 11n MCS rates supported by the RF profile, indexed by the MCS rate, ranging from 1 to 24, corresponding to rate MCS-0, MCS-1, ... MCS-23.

cLRFProfileMcsDataRateEntry.name: cLRFProfileMcsDataRateEntry
cLRFProfileMcsDataRateEntry.description: An entry containing MCS date rate information applicable to a particular profile.

cLRFProfileMcsName.name: cLRFProfileMcsName
cLRFProfileMcsName.description: This object uniquely identifies a RF Profile.

cLRFProfileMcsRate.name: cLRFProfileMcsRate
cLRFProfileMcsRate.description: This object uniquely identifies the MCS data rate for a particular profile.

cLRFProfileMcsRateSupport.name: cLRFProfileMcsRateSupport
cLRFProfileMcsRateSupport.description: This object is used to enable or disable the data rate. When this object is set to 'true' the MCS support is enabled. When this object is set to 'false' the MCS support is disabled..

ciscoLwappRFMIBCompliance.name: ciscoLwappRFMIBCompliance
ciscoLwappRFMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the SNMP entities that implement the ciscoLwappRFMIB module. This compliance is deprecated and replaced by ciscoLwappRFMIBComplianceVer1 .

ciscoLwappRFMIBComplianceVer1.name: ciscoLwappRFMIBComplianceVer1
ciscoLwappRFMIBComplianceVer1.description: The compliance statement for the SNMP entities that implement the ciscoLwappRFMIB module.

ciscoLwappRFMIBComplianceVer2.name: ciscoLwappRFMIBComplianceVer2
ciscoLwappRFMIBComplianceVer2.description: The compliance statement for the SNMP entities that implement the ciscoLwappRFMIB module. Added ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup2 to add object to raise trap when client count exceeds threshold and ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup3 to address DCA settings

ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup.name: ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup
ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup.description: This collection of objects specifies the configuration of RF parameters on the controller to be passed to an LWAPP AP.This config group ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup is deprecated and replaced by ciscoLwappRFConfigGroupVer1

ciscoLwappRFConfigGroupVer1.name: ciscoLwappRFConfigGroupVer1
ciscoLwappRFConfigGroupVer1.description: This collection of objects specifies the configuration of RF parameters on the controller to be passed to an LWAPP AP.

ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup1.name: ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup1
ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup1.description: This collection of objects specifies the configuration of RF parameters on the controller to be passed to an LWAPP AP.

ciscoLwappRFGlobalConfigGroup.name: ciscoLwappRFGlobalConfigGroup
ciscoLwappRFGlobalConfigGroup.description: This is the RF global config parameter.

ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup2.name: ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup2
ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup2.description: This object specifies the configuration of Trap threshold to be configured on the interface of an LWAPP AP.

ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup3.name: ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup3
ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup3.description: This object specifies the configuration DCA for RF Profiles.

ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup4.name: ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup4
ciscoLwappRFConfigGroup4.description: This object specifies the receiver start of packet threshold for RF Profiles.
